If the activity is measurably lower in the presence of the candidate compound than in its absence, then the compound has FBA inhibitory activity and is a candidate antibiotic and antiparasitic compound. The compound may also be screened with recombinant or isolated Class I FBA (for example, of human or mammalian origin) to determine cross-inhibition.
